Medicare Basics

Overview

   The Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS) administers
   Medicare, the nation's largest health insurance program, which covers
   39 million Americans.

   Medicare is a Health Insurance Program for people 65 years of age and
   older, some disabled people under 65 years of age, and people with
   End-Stage Renal Disease (permanent kidney failure treated with dialysis
   or a transplant).

   Medicare Eligibility and Enrollment

   What is Medicare?: provides information on what Medicare is.

   Who is Eligible for Medicare?: contains guidelines to determine whether
   or not you are eligible for Medicare.

   Enrolling in Medicare: explains how to sign up for Medicare Part A and
   B.

   General Enrollment Period: provides information on what the General
   Enrollment Period is and when you can enroll.

   Initial Enrollment Package: contains a copy of the initial enrollment
   package sent in the mail to new enrollees.

   Help with Your Medicare Account

   About Your Medicare Card: provides information on when you will receive
   your Medicare card, when to use the card and how to replace a lost
   card.

   Address Change: explains who to contact to change your address.

   Medicare Coverage and Billing

   Your Medicare Benefits: links to a publication providing a description
   of your health care coverage under Part A and Part B.

   How to File a Claim: If you see a doctor or supplier that does not
   accept assignment and had to pay for the service yourself, this
   provides the steps you should take to get reimbursed.

   Medicare Summary Notice: provides details on the redesign of the
   Medicare monthly benefits statements (Medicare Summary Notice - MSN),
   including instructions and examples on how to read the new form.
   Espanol - Resumen de Medicare

   Premiums and Costs

   Medicare Amounts for 2002: links to information on deductible,
   coinsurance and premium amounts for 2002.

   Help to Pay your Health Care Costs: identifies special programs,
   including prescription drug assistance programs, that are available to
   help Medicare Beneficiaries pay for their health care costs.

   Other Information

   Medicare Basics Publications: Links you to the site's Publications
   Page. You will be taken directly to the section containing "Medicare
   Basics" related publications.


